This paper belongs to the field of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on named entity recognition (NER) in biographical texts. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and its applications. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for NER, which suggests the sub-categories cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as likely options. Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of different NER tools, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper specifically deals with named entities, which is a sub-field of NLP, making cs.NE (Natural Language Processing and Computational Linguistics) another likely sub-category.
